name: Reebok Ragnar Las Vegas
intro:
Teams will start in the outskirts of the Mojave Desert, and run with views of their Las Vegas oasis in sight. Then, teams run through the city, hitting Red Rock Resort at exchange 12 where they can re-stock and refresh before heading out again into the night. You'll Run, Drive, Sleep? Repeat until you finish back at the Red Rock Resort and party pool-side with your team! To book and receive a special Ragnar rate, click here, or call 702-797-7625 or 866-767-7773 and use the code RCIRR16.
This race is a part of our Double Medal Series! Run Ragnar Relay Las Vegas and Wasatch Back to get the highly exclusive Saints & Sinners double medal. Or, complete any other Ragnar Relay in the series (not Wasatch Back or Trail) and pick up the Deuces Wild double medal.

Reebok Ragnar Relay Las Vegas is part of the Double Medal Series. Triple your bling in 2016 by running Reebok Ragnar Las Vegas and Reebok Ragnar Wasatch Back and earn yourself the highly exclusive Saints & Sinners Double Medal! You can also complete any other Reebok Ragnar (excluding Ragnar Trail and Reebok Ragnar Wasatch Back) and earn the Deuces Wild Double Medal! 

GREAT NEWS! All 2016 Reebok Ragnar Relay captains will be receiving free Reebok One Series running shoes!! As a captain, we know you are committed to going the distance and Reebok wants your feedback. Check out our Reebok Shoes page for more info!

charity:
We’re proud to partner with It Ain't Chemo as a charity partner of Ragnar Relay Las Vegas. It Ain't Chemo was created on the premise that people fighting cancer have needs not often met by other organizations or medical facilities. Using input from cancer patients and drawing on the experience of the organization’s founder, a cancer survivor himself, they provide cancer patients with comfort, care, supplies, advice and emotional support. They also organize fun experiences for their “Warriors” (cancer patients) that are designed to give them a break from their daily battle. As a group they try to be as hands on and available to their “Warriors" as possible and often form personal friendships that last far beyond the cancer battle. The It Ain’t Chemo group is comprised of a diverse collection of individuals with very unique backgrounds. They have firefighters, UFC fighters, military veterans and local personalities joining together to bring smiles to people in a tough situation.

 



Ragnar Las Vegas is just around the corner. Make the weekend even more meaningful by fundraising for a Ragnar charity partner or your favorite charity on everydayhero, the official fundraising platform of Ragnar Relay Series! 

Simply go here (or click on the everydayhero logo above) and choose your favorite charity – it’s that easy!  Your fundraising page will be created and you can start making every step count.

To date, the Ragnar community has fundraised over 1 million dollars so let's keep it going!

travel.content:
2016 Hotel Options - The Red Rock Casino Resort & Spa

The Red Rock Resort provides the ultimate Ragnar Las Vegas experience. As host to finish line and exchange 12 and only minutes away from the pre-race packet pickup, The Red Rock Resort provides a place for all your pre and post relay adventures. Red Rock Casino Resort & Spa provides the ultimate Las Vegas resort experience. The resort hotel provides an idyllic getaway just minutes from the world-renowned Las Vegas Strip. Ideally situated near the entrance to Red Rock Canyon National Recreation area, you couldn’t ask for a more intimate, yet exciting place to play, both indoors and out.

To book and receive a special Ragnar rate, click on the here, or call 702-797-7625 or 866-767-7773 and use the code RCIRR16.

         

About Red Rock Resort

Inspired by the natural beauty of the neighboring mountains, Red Rock Casino Resort & Spa pays homage to the elegant mid-century modern resorts that made Las Vegas famous. The design is classic, cool Las Vegas, reinvented for the 21st century. A recipient of the AAA Four Diamond Award since opening and named one of the world's best new hotels by Conde Nast Traveler magazine, Red Rock redefines casino resort architecture by incorporating natural light, a convenient layout and the comforts of a modern lifestyle, making for the perfect Las Vegas hotel rooms & Las Vegas suites.

 

Van Rental

Need to rent a van? Enterprise can hook you up!

 

Elevated Legs Rental

Turn your van into a recovery station! Our partners Elevated Legs are renting legs for $120 for the whole race - that's $20/person for a van of 6!

For more information check out: http://elevatedlegs.com/rent/ragnar/

*Be sure to rent your legs before Monday, October 31st to ensure delivery before the race!*

reg_system.name: Reebok Ragnar Las Vegas
reg_system.description: Teams will start at the top of Las Vegas Ski & Snowboard Resort, head down from 8500 feet into the valley, and run with views of the Las Vegas strip in sight. Then, teams run through the city, hitting Red Rock Resort at Exchange 12 where they can re-stock and refresh before heading out again into the night. You'll Run, Drive, Sleep? Repeat until you finish back at the Red Rock Resort and party pool-side with your team!GREAT NEWS! All 2016 Reebok Ragnar Relay captains will be recieving free Reebok One Series running shoes!! As a captain, we know you are committed to going the distance and Reebok wants your feedback. Check out our Reebok Shoes page for more info!Reebok Ragnar Relay Las Vegas is part of the Double Medal Series. Triple your bling in 2016 by running Reebok Ragnar Las Vegas and Reebok Ragnar Wasatch Back and earn yourself the highly exclusive Saints & Sinners Double Medal! You can also complete any other Reebok Ragnar (excluding Ragnar Trail and Reebok Ragnar Wasatch Back) and earn the Deuces Wild Double Medal!
